—would demonstrate to Moscow a further U.S.
                        capacity to improve our relations with Peking, which could have a healthy
                        effect on the Soviet attitude towards the U.S.;

—would provide the Administration with the capability to make maximum use
                        of actions to liberalize and promote trade in support of other objectives in
                        our relations with the USSR;

—urgent action is needed to permit MFN for
                        Romania if the United States is to be able formally to participate in
                        negotiating terms under which Romania may accede to the GATT;

—the offer of MFN without credit and
                        guarantee facilities would have much less potency as a bargaining tool with
                        Communist governments;
